{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 17:12:51.412676", "event": "llm_end", "text": " Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"router_core_3\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"frr_service_down\"]\n\nRecommended next actions I suggest to the operations team (not part of the submission):\n1. On router_core_3:\n   - Inspect FRR logs (journalctl -u frr) and /var/log/frr/* for crash traces or configuration errors.\n   - Attempt to restart FRR (systemctl restart frr) and verify status (systemctl status frr).\n   - After FRR is running, verify OSPF adjacencies (show ip ospf neighbor) and that 10.200.0.0/24 is being advertised/learned.\n2. On server_access_router and core routers:\n   - Verify OSPF neighbor states and routing tables (show ip route) to confirm propagation.\n   - Run traceroutes from representative user hosts to server-farm addresses to confirm end-to-end reachability restored.\n3. Post-recovery:\n   - Correlate FRR downtime with recent changes or resource issues; consider alerts to detect FRR service failures in future.\n4. Investigate secondary host-to-host packet loss anomalies separately.\n\nIf you want, I can draft exact CLI commands and the sequence to safely restart FRR and validate routes, or help interpret FRR logs if you provide them.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2336, "output_tokens": 287, "total_tokens": 2623, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
